description: This is a beautiful American Trader Red and White Cedar strip canoe, the Trapper 14 model.  A classic lightweight tandem canoe, stable, fast and visually striking, this canoe is well suited for two adults. The traditional lines of this canoe take the paddler back to the simple origins of canoeing.  It's perfect for the weekend trip and its small size and good looks also make it an ideal canoe to display. A great choice for day tripping, bird watching, photography, and recreational paddling. With it's graceful, elegant lines the Trapper is also an excellent display model for homes, lodges, restaurants and stores. The length is 14 feet, 34-inch beam, and it weighs 59 lbs. Two Special Laminated Ash and Cherry Beavertail Paddles are also included.  This canoe also has the extended decks which fit over the internal stem and the outwales are extended to a point beyond the recurve. Brass stem band is finished under the gunnels.  Has hand-laced rawhide seats, sculpted carrying yokes, thwarts, and handles.  Hand-crafted, a blend of old and new design elements with traditional and modern skills and materials, a fully functional canoe that is also an amazingly beautiful work of art.  Stunning to look at and a joy to paddle. This canoe has been on the water a grand total of 3 times, on a pond.  It has a few scuffs from transport and storage but there is absolutely nothing wrong with it and it looks absolutely awesome!  This canoe brand new would cost over $4300, plus about another $500 for delivery! Well, here it is, ready to float and/or display.  We're asking $3400, also trades considered for gold or silver coins or bullion, 357 mag snubnose revolver, 45 auto pistol, firewood (oak, locust, or hickory only), goats, laying hens, mallard ducks, other useful farm or outdoor type items, let me know what you might have in mind.  Delivery available. Drop me an email with your questions, I'll get right back to you.  Thanks for looking!
title: American Traders Trapper 14 cedar strip canoe
